==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|everichon|lang=enm}}, equivalent to {{compound|every|one|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-everyone.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Pronoun===
{{en-pron}}

# Every [[person]].

====Usage notes====
* This can be used loosely to mean "the majority of people," though linguistic purists will protest.

